We had a brainstorm session to evaluate the course.

Leon proposed:
- important to be more explicit about what the students can expect from the course and what we expect from the students
--> update study guide, course manual, put lecture notes on our websites

What to expect from students:
- we should communicate to AI students that either they should already know probability measure theory, or be prepared to work hard to catch up with this requirement

Patrick proposed:
- use standard Borel spaces everywhere
- move lecture 2 online as a crash course for AI students, this will make some space for one more lecture
- perhaps add an overview to what else is out there as a final lecture

Patrick & I proposed:
- streamline ordering (delay SCMs until after CBNS are done, which should be about lecture 7)

I proposed:
- add proper references throughout the lecture notes


See also feedback.txt for detailed feedback on lectures and exercices
